        "body":  "﻿Manual salvage completed and published to `main` in `428594a` (`docs: record default clean variance pass`).\n\nThe queued Codex executor correctly halted before any build sample because its workspace sandbox could not create `B:\\sdk\\rge-clean-default-variance-ISSUE-339-sample1` (`UnauthorizedAccessException`). I preserved the blocked dispatch context under gitignored root `.ai/dispatch-ISSUE-339/orchestrator-blocked/`.\n\nRoot-shell salvage then ran the three required fresh isolated plain `DefaultCleanRelease` samples with separate `B:\\sdk` targets:\n\n| Sample | Wall | Cargo `Finished` | Exit | Verdict |\n|---:|---:|---|---:|---|\n| 1 | 109.273s | 1m 48s | 0 | PASS |\n| 2 | 115.303s | 1m 55s | 0 | PASS |\n| 3 | 108.280s | 1m 48s | 0 | PASS |\n\nAll generated commands were explicit `cargo build --release -p ...` package lists with no `--workspace`; the resolver reported 92 included / 5 excluded packages and `rge-tool-wasm-bench` included. All sample targets were verified under `B:\\sdk`, removed, and verified absent.\n\nResult: `DefaultCleanRelease` clean-build gate is now recorded as a recorder-host provisional PASS at max 115.303s vs \u003c=120s. Follow-up task 97 is automation hygiene for an explicit Codex executor external-scratch option, so future `B:\\sdk` measurement dispatches do not need manual salvage.\r\n",
